BE IN THE HOSPITAL, RIGHT?

10:27.433 --> 10:29.300
I MEAN, WHAT'S THE POINT?

10:32.567 --> 10:34.067
THEN AGAIN,
I GUESS NOBODY

10:34.100 --> 10:35.667
LIKES TO BE AROUND
THE SMELL OF ROT.

10:35.700 --> 10:36.667
DANA--

10:36.700 --> 10:38.500
NO, LARA, IT'S TRUE.

10:38.533 --> 10:41.800
I HOPE
YOU KNOW THAT.

10:41.833 --> 10:44.133
I DON'T WANT THOSE.

10:44.167 --> 10:45.900
THEY BUNCH UP TOO MUCH.
I WANT THE GREEN ONES.

10:48.233 --> 10:50.300
OKAY.

10:57.500 --> 10:58.600
THE GREEN ONES.

11:04.900 --> 11:06.067
ANYTHING ELSE?

11:16.467 --> 11:18.333
[SNIFFLING]

11:24.733 --> 11:26.333
HERE YOU GO...

11:30.067 --> 11:32.300
HERE YOU GO. THANKS.

11:32.333 --> 11:34.333
COME ON, PACE, PACE, PACE.
MOVE IT.

11:34.367 --> 11:35.433
AH, GOOD MORNING.

11:35.467 --> 11:36.433
GOOD MORNING.

11:36.467 --> 11:37.467
IS IT FOR ONE?

11:37.500 --> 11:38.467
YES.

11:38.500 --> 11:39.467
JENNY, COULD YOU SIT--

11:39.500 --> 11:41.467
OH, MY GOD, HI!
HI!

11:41.500 --> 11:43.133
IT'S SO NICE TO SEE YOU!
IT'S NICE TO SEE YOU.

11:43.167 --> 11:44.667
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

11:44.700 --> 11:45.967
UH-OH, YOU DIDN'T
GET MY MESSAGE?

11:46.067 --> 11:47.133
NO.

11:47.167 --> 11:48.133
I'M HERE
TO SEE YOU.

11:48.167 --> 11:49.767
OH, MY GOD,
WOW, UM...

11:49.800 --> 11:51.767
OH, THANK YOU.

11:51.800 --> 11:52.867
I'LL SIT DOWN.

11:52.900 --> 11:54.867
OKAY, GREAT.

11:54.900 --> 11:56.533
AND YOU SHOULD SIT DOWN.

11:57.533 --> 11:58.933
I KNOW IT'S A BIT UNUSUAL

11:58.967 --> 12:01.133
FOR A PUBLISHER
TO JUMP ON A PLANE

12:01.167 --> 12:03.933
AND FLY ACROSS THE COUNTRY
TO SEE A WRITER.

12:03.967 --> 12:05.300
WELL, I'M JUST GRATEFUL

12:05.333 --> 12:07.433
THAT YOU TOOK THE TIME
TO READ IT.

12:07.467 --> 12:09.100
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT
MY DAUGHTER'S LIKE.

12:09.133 --> 12:12.533
REBECCA WOULDN'T STOP
UNTIL I'D READ EVERY WORD.

12:12.567 --> 12:13.867
AND I'M VERY GRATEFUL
THAT I DID.

12:13.900 --> 12:15.200
HOW IS REBECCA?

12:15.233 --> 12:16.400
UH, JENNY...

12:16.433 --> 12:17.867
YES?

12:17.900 --> 12:19.400
TABLE SEVEN
WOULD LIKE HER CHECK.

12:19.433 --> 12:21.633
BILLIE,
IT WOULD BE SUPER FANTASTIC

12:21.667 --> 12:22.933
IF YOU COULD ACTUALLY
COVER FOR ME

12:22.967 --> 12:25.533
JUST FOR
FIVE MINUTES.

12:25.567 --> 12:27.133
HERE YOU GO, UM...

12:27.167 --> 12:28.867
AND THEN THIS.
I'M SO SORRY.

12:31.700 --> 12:33.133
SORRY.

12:33.167 --> 12:36.167
LET ME GET
RIGHT DOWN TO BUSINESS.

12:36.200 --> 12:37.633
OKAY.

12:37.667 --> 12:39.067
WE WANT TO PUBLISH YOUR BOOK.

12:39.067 --> 12:40.567
NEXT FALL.

12:40.600 --> 12:41.633
I WANT TO LINE IT UP

12:41.667 --> 12:43.233
AGAINST SOME OF THE BIG HITTERS,

12:43.267 --> 12:45.433
MAKE THE CRITICS
REALLY TAKE NOTICE.

12:48.800 --> 12:50.433
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

12:50.467 --> 12:52.267
YEAH,

12:52.300 --> 12:55.167
AND IT WAS IMPORTANT TO ME
WE HAVE THIS CHANCE TO TALK,

12:55.200 --> 12:56.700
BECAUSE I HAVE TO
ASK YOU SOMETHING, JENNY.

12:56.733 --> 12:59.133
I'M SORRY.

12:59.167 --> 13:00.333
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

13:00.367 --> 13:01.767
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

13:01.800 --> 13:04.767
HOW MUCH OF THE NOVEL IS TRUE?

13:04.800 --> 13:07.433
I'M IMAGINING THAT A LOT
OF THE THINGS IN THIS BOOK

13:07.467 --> 13:08.933
ACTUALLY HAPPENED TO YOU.

13:08.967 --> 13:14.533
UM, YEAH, I MEAN,
IT CUTS CLOSE TO THE BONE.

13:14.567 --> 13:16.400
NOT SINCE
BASTARD OUT OF CAROLINA

13:16.433 --> 13:18.467
HAVE I BEEN
SO THOROUGHLY CONVINCED.

13:18.500 --> 13:22.767
THE WAY
YOU HANDLE TRAUMA,

13:22.800 --> 13:25.467
AND THE LANDSCAPE
OF THAT POOR GIRL'S MIND...

13:25.500 --> 13:26.933
YOU WERE A CUTTER, RIGHT?

13:26.967 --> 13:29.167
