NEVER SAY,

13:29.200 --> 13:32.267
BUT, YOU KNOW,
FROM WHAT YOU WROTE...

13:32.300 --> 13:34.267
I WAS, BUT I'M NOT NOW.

13:36.100 --> 13:38.200
WE'RE GOING TO SEND YOU
ON A BOOK TOUR,

13:38.233 --> 13:40.100
AND I DON'T WANT YOU TO BE
AFRAID TO TALK ABOUT THAT.

13:40.133 --> 13:43.067
I DON'T KNOW WHY
I'D TALK ABOUT ME,

13:43.067 --> 13:44.600
BECAUSE THE BOOK IS FICTION.

13:44.633 --> 13:47.667
I UNDERSTAND THAT,
BUT, UNFORTUNATELY, JENNY,

13:47.700 --> 13:49.367
PEOPLE AREN'T BUYING
LITERARY FICTION

13:49.400 --> 13:50.600
THE WAY THEY USED TO.

13:50.633 --> 13:52.367
IN TODAY'S CLIMATE,

13:52.400 --> 13:54.233
SURVIVOR MEMOIRS
HAVE A MUCH BETTER CHANCE

13:54.267 --> 13:55.667
OF BREAKING OUT
AND REACHING AN AUDIENCE--

13:55.700 --> 13:58.300
JENNY, OKAY, CUT IT,
PRINT IT, MOVING ON.

13:58.333 --> 13:59.833
COME ON.

13:59.867 --> 14:01.533
KIT...

14:01.567 --> 14:03.767
KIT, I'M SORRY.
BILLIE...

14:03.800 --> 14:06.567
I'D LIKE YOU GUYS
TO MEET JAN MARTIN,

14:06.600 --> 14:08.433
WHO'S HERE
FROM SIMON & SCHUSTER.

14:08.467 --> 14:10.667
SHE FLEW IN FROM NEW YORK
TO TALK TO ME ABOUT MY NOVEL.

14:10.700 --> 14:12.233
HI.
HEY.

14:12.267 --> 14:14.333
HI. OH, UH, BILLIE...

14:14.367 --> 14:16.867
